Responsive Portfolio Template
This is a multi-page portfolio site I built to practice clean frontend architecture and responsive design. While the content currently uses placeholder text, the project served as a great exercise in structural CSS, modular HTML, and fixing real-world deployment issues.

🛠 Key Technical Skills 
DemonstratedSystemic CSS Architecture: I used a utility-first approach for the styling, creating a consistent system for spacing (py-1 through py-4), button design (btn-main, btn-dark, and btn-light), and color themes (bg-dark, bg-main, and bg-light) that can be easily scaled or modified.  

Responsive Layouts: The site is fully responsive, utilizing CSS Grid and Flexbox to ensure complex layouts—like the "Specialization" grid and "Appreciation" section—stack cleanly on mobile devices.  

Custom JavaScript Interactivity: Instead of relying on heavy libraries, I wrote a custom TypeWriter class in vanilla JavaScript to handle the dynamic text cycling on the landing page.  

Problem Solving & Debugging: I spent time refactoring the project to fix critical pathing issues for assets (CSS and images) and corrected invalid CSS syntax to ensure cross-browser stability.  

📂 Project Highlights
index.html: A high-impact landing page featuring a full-viewport hero section.

work.html: A project gallery layout with CSS-animated overlays for a professional look and feel.

about.html: Includes a structured biography section and technical skill progress bars.

Contact.html: Serves as a functional communication hub featuring a CSS Grid-based layout for user inquiries, alongside integrated contact details and Netlify-ready form handling for serverless deployment.

main.css: A comprehensive stylesheet that manages global transitions, hover states, and mobile-specific overrides.

📝 Note on Content
This project was created as a structural template. It currently utilizes Lorem Ipsum for text and some of assets provided by my course instructor to test grid responsiveness and image-loading optimization.